column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Cweilsaem has a favor to ask.
Deliver the small package to W'sondidi.
Drink the golden syrup near W'sondidi.
Speak with Cweilsaem.
It's <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>, isn't it? I was about to head to Kokkol's Forge to drop something off, but I think you'd be more welcome than I.
As it turns out, the recipient is something of an admirer of yours. I'm sure she'd be thrilled to have you make the delivery.
Thank you! Here's the package, all set to be delivered to W'sondidi.
W'sondidi is waiting for her delivery at Kokkol's Forge. I wish I could see the look on her face when she realizes it's you!
Hello th─<Emphasis>eep</Emphasis>! It's you! The one and only <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>! Am I dreaming?
A delivery for me? But why would someone as famous and important as you be delivering my package?
Oh, now I'm just being rude. I must thank you properly! If only I had known you'd be coming, I could have prepared something for you...
Silly me, there's something for you right here! This package contains a bottle of golden syrup. It's yours if you want it.
It's an alchemical medicine to rejuvenate the wearied body. You must need something like that after running around and saving the <Emphasis>entire world</Emphasis>.
I won't hear “no” for an answer, so drink it down! You deserve it far more than I do!
Please drink the syrup before you go. I'd never forgive myself if this delivery contributed to your exhaustion.
W'sondidi will be disappointed if you do not drink the medicine where she can see you.
The medicine is much sweeter than you were expecting.
What will you say?
It's delicious!
The taste is a bit...much.
I'm glad! I hope it nourishes your body along with pleasing your palate.
It <Emphasis>is</Emphasis> medicine, after all. Regardless of the flavor, I hope it does your body some good.
That reminds me, I had your comrade G'raha try some as well.
He seemed to quite enjoy it─said it was like drinking sweet ambrosia. I couldn't help but wonder what sort of medicine he had been forced to drink before...
Anyway, I'm afraid that's all I have to offer you. I swear, if Cweilsaem doesn't compensate you properly I just might─ Well, never mind that! Please take proper care of yourself out there.
Make sure Cweilsaem pays you properly!
All finished, then? She works herself too hard, that W'sondidi. The medicine I sent should be good for her.
Though I must say, you're looking rather more chipper than when you left.
Now that I look at you, you don't look too well yourself. Are you feeling all right?
What? She gave the syrup to you? Well, if that cheered her up, I suppose that's as good as any medicine. In any case, here's a little something as thanks for your help.
